        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-25T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-25T02:00:00-05:00" n="896" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d896">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/4–2546: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-25T10:00:00+03:00">April 25, 1946—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 25—9:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1325. ReDeptel 688, April 12.<note n="18" xml:id="d896fn18">Not printed.</note>
                    Benninghoff apparently unable to telegraph Dept from Dairen. He sent following
                    telegram to Soviet FonOff which FonOff repeated to us in its note 650, April 21:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“To Deputy Minister Lozovsky. American Embassy No. 17. Arrived April 7.
                            Cordially met by local authorities. Am doing everything necessary for
                            speedy opening. Please discuss with Soviet authorities question of
                            telegraphic communications between Embassy and Consulates in China, also
                            Washington. Inform Washington. Benninghoff.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
